For those who love a little crunchy feeling in their palate, an Oreo dessert may be the perfect option for that. It is definitely a winner for sweet tooth. For you to enjoy this dessert, you can make it at home using the following ingredients;  Preparation Step 1 Take a large zip-lock bag and place all the Oreo cookies inside. Seal bag shut and place them on the counter. Step 2 Using a rolling pin, crush the cookies until they are small chunks. Be careful not to beat them to fine crumbs. Set aside. Step 3 Divide 1/3 and set aside. Add the remaining cookie crumbs into a baking pan then pour the melted butter over the crumbs and mix well to combine. Step 4 Press into the pan to form a crust. Step 5 In a medium bowl, whisk together the 2 pudding mix and milk. Then cover and place in the fridge. Step 6 Blend the cream cheese until smooth then slowly add in the powdered sugar. Fold then spread the mixture over the cookie crust. Step 7 Take chocolate pudding and spread it over the cream cheese mixture. Spread the other container of Cool Whip over the chocolate pudding layer. Step 8 Sprinkle the top with the remaining Oreo cookie crumbs. Step 9 Cover and chill in the fridge at least 2 hours before serving. Enjoy with friends and family.